 life and poetry and inspired by the publication of this biography the europe center is co sponsoring the public workshop nelly sachs migration and memory poetry and context at stanford on march 8th in addition to dramatic poetry readings and reception this event will include a book signing by author aris fioretos books will also be available for purchase related links nelly sachs migration and memory poetry and context march 8 2012 fsi stanford the europe center workshop amir eshel aris fioretos deniz gokturk axel englund anna westerstahl stenport leslie morris lucy alford andrew utter pdf+ conference agenda flyer available html+ nelly sachs flight and metamorphosis http www sup org book cgi id 2074 search fsi search within everything courses events fellowships news op eds people publications research other pages news of interest a newly released film tells the story of us nuclear policy october 12 2011 fsi stanford cisac announcement sachs mixes laughter human rights cddrl phr in the news stanford daily on february 11 2010 rehabilitation never tried at gitmo some return to terrorism as hundreds are released cisac in the news washington times on february 19 2009 pesd carbon storage project database released july 1 2008 pesd news spice wins $25000 goldman sachs foundation prize spice in the news stanford report on march 19 2008 natural gas and geopolitics from 1970 to 2040 book released july 5 2006 pesd press release support map & directions contact rss+ rss xml feeds freeman spogli institute for international studies encina hall 616 serra st stanford ca 94305 6055 tel 650 723 4581 fax 650 725 2592 mail code 6055
